reviews.text:
First time visit that's worth repeating. Over 30 self-serve taps with a very good selection of micro-brews, and some novel craft cocktail offerings as well. Excellent service, and nice Summer atmosphere with inside & outside seating.
The adjacent Village lawn area has live music on some weekdays, which was an added bonus for sitting outside and it isn't so loud to drown out talking. "Insiders" can also enjoy sport events on a big screen  right by the self-serve beer taps.
Didn't try their pizzas on the first time visit, but will do so next time.

Amazing drinks, pizza, and atmosphere! Michael is a great host and the whole operation is top notch. They use a self-pour draft system for a lot of their offerings, which lets you experiment with 30 beer/wine/cocktail options by the oz. They also make delicious handcrafted cocktails and have a huge screen for playing multiple football games at once. Perfect for fantasy!

This is a great tap room. With nice sofa and dog friendly. The waitress gal was super friendly asking me for what I needed. I quit drinking but she was able to offer me a nice cup of lemon soda water for 2 bucks and I got this well designed aluminum cut of ice water to go in the end. Many dog lovers came to say hi to my dog Ares while I was there. If I also drink beer this would be one of the best stops for it.
LOVE Jack, Wish he was here for the Kentucky derby. Drinks delish, Food always amazing. My favorite watering hole for family, friends and clients!

Great place! Great atmosphere, music, seating, delicious pizza. The assortment of beers on tap is phenomenal and a great way to try different things, and the full bar has everything you could want. Bartenders are very friendly and helpful. Always playing the games on the big 4-way split screen - even 4 NFL games at once! There are also a lot of card and board games to play, so you‚Äôll never be bored.

Have been here several times, the pizza is good quality and they also have a good GF crust. The pour-your-own-beer is a fun gimmick I can appreciate, on-demand beer and a large variety of drinks, including seltzers and cocktails.
This time however, I only enjoyed the beer on my tab. I asked for the pass cards at the bar and poured my rounds. I wanted to get a few of the cocktails but either of the bartenders were fumbling through orders, with a long line of people stacking up at the bar, so I passed.
When it came time to close out, I‚Äôm given my bill and then ‚Äúit‚Äôs going to ask you a little question,‚Äù comes out. Replay this scenario‚Ä¶. I poured my own drinks. Bussed my own table. And put my own glasses in the dirty dishes tray. I didn‚Äôt order a cocktail and had no interaction with the bartender aside from opening and closing a tab. The times that I did, they were too busy or inattentive.
So, I decided, ‚ÄòNo Tip,‚Äô fair, right?
This employee decided to flip back the screen while the payment is still processing- that way he sees this, and not only audibly scoffs, rolls his eyes, as I am walking away he goes, ‚Äúhey right on man,‚Äù and puts his fist out for a fist bump. I fist bump back because I have thick skin and ai genuinely understand when a tip is appropriate or not,  it that was some jerk attitude that will seriously make me reconsider coming back to that place.

If your establishment is a counter service restaurant where customers BUS their OWN tables and POUR their OWN drinks, either pay them a fair wage, or train them to do their job better, different, or with an expectation that ‚Äòno you‚Äôre not getting even 10% of a bar tab where the customer did all of the work.‚Äô Super irritating.
